ub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=galtinrandayn>Galtin Randayn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/26/03 9:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3580.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Personal character vs roleplay standards</span><hr size=1> Not so hypothetical situation.<br>
<br>
Applicant to a guild has all the personal qualities you are looking for in a guildmember.  Guildmates have grouped/raided with him a several occasions and he passes all the &quot;character&quot; tests.  However, the applicant has a friviolous, non-roleplaying character name.  Were their name to get discussed on this board, good chance it would be ridiculed.<br>
<br>
So what do you do?  Focus on character, ignore the name, and give them an invite?  Or do you enforce roleplay standards and not invite a nice person into the guild?  In most guilds, a player's personal qualities are the most important factor when determining if they get an invite into the guild.  However, if a guild invites folks in with a silly, frivolous name, then the perception of the FV community towards the guild may get lowered (i.e. that guild will let anyone in).  This has the possibility of hurting future recruiting.  <br>
<br>
Interested in hearing what the Soapbox has to say on this.  If you reply, indicate if you RP or don't RP. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=loganhex>LoganHex</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/26/03 9:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3580.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Personal character vs roleplay standards</span><hr size=1> When I first started on Firiona Vie I was all about roleplaying. Unfortunately a large majority of the other players I met were not so I began roleplaying less and less.<br>
<br>
Having said that, inappropriate names on any server irk me. It spoils the nature of the game and shows a blatant disregard for the rules as well as a lack of imagination (in most cases at least).<br>
<br>
It is your guild never the less which means it is your decision. Which is more important? Obviously the person behind the character is more important than the name. Perhaps he roleplays rather well and simply made a mistake by selecting a silly name when he created his character. <br>
<br>
As far as guild reputation is concerned I can only speak for myself here. I was once a member of the Peacekeepers Alliance which was supposed to be a roleplaying guild. We had a couple of members with inappropriate names (Icecoffy springs to mind here). I personally felt as if having a member with an inappropriate name such as that hurt our status as a roleplaying guild. Of course not many of us roleplayed anyway.<br>
<br>
To summarize, will it hurt you? Probably in a minor way. Will it give people the impression that you will let anyone in? Not if the misnamed person roleplays well outside of their name. Would I let them in? No. Rules are rules after all.<br>
<br>
Just my take. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eliezeroferudin>Eliezer of Erudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Order of Crimson Hands</span><br>  Posts: 1499<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/26/03 9:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3580.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Personal character vs roleplay standards</span><hr size=1> $50 can fix the problem. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kuladen>kuladen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FV's Babblefish</span><br>  Posts: 1979<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/26/03 10:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3580.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.inkbard.com/art/kuladenclrthmb.jpg  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Personal character vs roleplay standards</span><hr size=1> My Rl name is Beeker. Not literally, but when joining my fraternity it was assigned to me, and it stuck. My friends call me Beeker. I don't turn my head when someone says Will. I turn when someone says Beeker. The people at work call me Beeker.<br>
