However, though a name can be important, it depends on the name. Can the person make up an IC reason why they might have that name. Can it be described as a nickname type of name he might of been given? For instance, if a person's name is Killbane, well, I'm sure something could be made up to explain the name away. Its all in how creative you are. I don't think you should shun this person out of your guild for a mistake they made when they were first starting out when they didn't realize that the name counted for anything. Not knowing the name, I cannot offer any suggestions to explain it away, but I'm sure, if he's a clever person, he can figure out something. I do not think he should be required to pay to have it changed. Its somewhat sad that the naming conventions -- the ruleset for naming that FV has supposedly isn't more strictly adhered to, because then perhaps a person could help the other person out by petitioning the name. I know that some GM's do make others change their names.. I have a friend who was required to change his name, because his name was based on a historical character. However, with all the Legaloses, and Legolaases and whatever have you, its obvious that this really isn't enforced unless someone makes a stink about it. For instance; Someone had the name DrFrankenfurter and I hear a GM refused to change it and said it was ok. Um. Since when? Didn't he see Rocky Horror? Anyhow.<br>
